Preheat your #oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Trim the @green beans{150%g}, then cut into thirds.

Peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves} (or use a #garlic press). Zest the @lime{1/2} and cut into wedges.

== Meatballs ==

In a #large bowl{}, combine the @panko breadcrumbs{10%g}, @salt{1/4%tsp} and @water{2%tbsp} for the breadcrumbs, then add the @British beef mince{240%g} and half the garlic.

Season with @pepper{} and mix together with your hands. Roll into even-sized balls, 5 per person, and pop onto a #baking tray{}.

When the #oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until browned on the outside and cooked through, ~{12-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince. They're cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

== Noodles ==

Meanwhile, bring a #large saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/4%tsp}.

When boiling, add the @egg noodle nests{2} to the water and cook until tender, ~{4%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and run under cold water to stop them sticking together.

== Stir-Fry ==

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #large frying pan{}.

Once hot, add the green beans and stir-fry until slightly charred, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Add the remaining garlic and cook for ~{1%minute}.

Stir in the @red pepper chilli jelly{50%g}, @ketjap manis{25%ml}, @soy sauce{15%ml} and @water{100%ml} for the sauce. Bring to the boil, then reduce to a simmer and cook until slightly reduced, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add the cooked noodles and meatballs to the #stir-fry pan{} and stir until everything's well coated in the sauce.

Add a squeeze of lime juice to taste.

Share your meatballs and noodles between your bowls.

Finish with a sprinkling of lime zest and serve with any remaining lime wedges for squeezing over.

Enjoy!